<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Hack the SEC</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A good plot for, like, an insider-trad=
ing Hollywood thriller would be if the villains hacked into the computers o=
f the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission. The SEC, after all, is maybe=
 the world=E2=80=99s greatest repository of material information about publ=
ic companies. Companies are constantly filing earnings releases, merger ann=
ouncements, management changes, proxy fights, all sorts of material news on=
 the SEC=E2=80=99s Edgar=C2=A0system. If you hacked into Edgar you could =
=E2=80=A6=C2=A0well, <em>in a movie</em>, I guess you could delay every fil=
ing by like 10 minutes, to give you a chance to read and trade on it? In th=
e real world most of this stuff gets announced after market hours, and anyw=
ay it mostly goes out on non-Edgar press wires too, so this probably wouldn=
=E2=80=99t work that well.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">You know w=
hat would work, though? There are companies that provide software for publi=
c companies to use to make Edgar filings, to =E2=80=9CEdgarize=E2=80=9D the=
ir press releases and other documents so that they comply with SEC formatti=
ng requirements. These services frequently=C2=A0<em>store </em>companies=E2=
=80=99=C2=A0material information for a while as it is being finalized, befo=
re it is filed and made public on Edgar.=C2=A0You could hack=C2=A0<em>them:=
</em></p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Servicers provide pro=
prietary, cloud-based software platforms to facilitate public companies=E2=
=80=99 filing of periodic and other reports with the SEC. The Servicers=E2=
=80=99 public company clients=E2=80=99 filings include, among other things,=
 Forms 8-K and related exhibits, which consist of press releases containing=
 the public companies=E2=80=99 earnings announcements. The=C2=A0Servicers=
=E2=80=99 public company clients can use the Servicers=E2=80=99 software pl=
atforms to create, edit, and submit their filings to the SEC via the SEC=E2=
=80=99s EDGAR filing system. ...</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Typically,=
 the Servicers=E2=80=99 public company clients begin the filing process for=
 an earnings announcement by loading a draft earnings announcement onto the=
 Servicer=E2=80=99s platform. Once loaded, the public company client can ed=
it the draft earnings announcement on the Servicer=E2=80=99s platform, befo=
re finalizing the earnings announcement and releasing the final version to =
the public via a newswire, and filing the announcement with the SEC as an a=
ttachment to a Form 8-K called =E2=80=9CExhibit 99.1.=E2=80=9D There is gen=
erally a window of several hours or days between the time that the public c=
ompany client uploads the pre-release earnings announcement onto the=C2=A0S=
ervicer=E2=80=99s platform and the time at which the client publicly dissem=
inates the final earnings announcement through a newswire and the filing of=
 the Form 8-K with the SEC.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Th=
at is from <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/2612325=
7.256657/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9saXRpZ2F0aW9uL2NvbXBsYWludHMvMjAyMS9jb2=
1wLXByMjAyMS0yNjUucGRm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBe9630876" itemprop=3D"Story=
Link" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; te=
xt-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-col=
or: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">an SEC co=
mplaint</a> accusing five Russians of hacking into two different (unnamed) =
companies that provide Edgarizing and filing services for public companies.=
 (Here is <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/26123257=
.256657/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9uZXdzL3ByZXNzLXJlbGVhc2UvMjAyMS0yNjU/607=
f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB6e80b387" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemsco=
pe" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !impor=
tant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom=
-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">the SEC=E2=80=99s announcement</a>;=
 there are also <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/26=
123257.256657/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuanVzdGljZS5nb3YvdXNhby1tYS9wci9ydXNzaWFuLW5hd=
GlvbmFsLWV4dHJhZGl0ZWQtcm9sZS1oYWNraW5nLWFuZC1pbGxlZ2FsLXRyYWRpbmctc2NoZW1l=
/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBb8095ae3" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"ite=
mscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !i=
mportant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bo=
ttom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">federal criminal charges</a>.)=
=C2=A0One of them, Ivan Yermakov, allegedly =E2=80=9Cserved as a Russian mi=
litary intelligence officer in the Russian Federation=E2=80=99s Main Intell=
igence Directorate of the General Staff (=E2=80=98GRU=E2=80=99)=E2=80=9D an=
d in 2018 was charged by federal prosecutors =E2=80=9Cfor his alleged roles=
 in a hacking conspiracy involving gaining unauthorized access into the com=
puters of U.S. persons and entities involved in the 2016 U.S. presidential =
election.=E2=80=9D In this caper, he allegedly hacked into the services=E2=
=80=99 computers, stole pre-release earnings announcements, and gave them t=
o the other defendants to trade:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;=
">If the pre-release earnings announcement indicated that the public compan=
y client=E2=80=99s stock=C2=A0price was likely to increase, then the Trader=
 Defendants bought stock in the company or CFDs referencing the company. If=
 the pre-release earnings announcement indicated that the public company cl=
ient=E2=80=99s stock price was likely to decline, then the Trader Defendant=
s sold short shares of the company=E2=80=99s stock or sold CFDs referencing=
 the company. =E2=80=A6</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Trader Defendan=
ts used the information hacked and deceptively-obtained from the Servicers=
=E2=80=99 systems by Yermakov to realize at least $82.5 million in illicit =
profits between February 2018 and August 2020.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"=
margin: 16px 0;">This was actually a bit less lucrative than a previous <a =
href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/26123257.256657/aHR0c=
HM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMTUtMDgtMTEvd2h5LW5v=
dC1pbnNpZGVyLXRyYWRlLW9uLWV2ZXJ5LWNvbXBhbnktP2NtcGlkPUJCRDEyMjEyMV9NT05FWVN=
UVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIxMT=
IyMSZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBdf4dd287" ite=
mprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"colo=
r: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; bor=
der-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #c=
cc;"> big hacker-insider-trading case</a>, in which the hackers got into th=
e=C2=A0<em>news wires=C2=A0</em>that publish press releases, but I enjoy it=
 more because it is a little closer to the ironic =E2=80=9Chacking the SEC =
itself=E2=80=9D scenario. There is a pipeline by which information moves fr=
om being secret to being public, and if you can hack into that pipeline you=
=E2=80=99ll get a lot of good stuff.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Pretty=
 good stuff, anyway.=C2=A0That previous case led to a <a href=3D"https://li=
nk.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/26123257.256657/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21=
iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMTktMTEtMjYva25vd2luZy10aGUtZnV0dXJlLW=
lzbi10LXRoYXQtaGVscGZ1bD9jbXBpZD1CQkQxMjIxMjFfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtP=
WVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMTEyMjEmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWdu=
PW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBae7b34e1" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" i=
temscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-deco=
ration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #00=
0000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> delightful acad=
emic study</a> finding that knowing every company=E2=80=99s earnings in adv=
ance was <em>useful</em>, but not=C2=A0<em>that=C2=A0</em>useful, because, =
despite the SEC=E2=80=99s casual discussion above, it=E2=80=99s not that ea=
sy to tell by reading an earnings release whether it =E2=80=9Cindicated=C2=
=A0that the public company client=E2=80=99s stock=C2=A0price was likely to =
increase=E2=80=9D or decline. Often the news in an earnings release is pric=
ed in! Here, the SEC complaint has=C2=A0a few case studies =E2=80=9Cof the =
more than 500 instances of trading before earnings announcements on the bas=
is of hacked information by the Trader Defendants between at least February=
 2018 and August 2020=E2=80=9D; the traders made money in each of these cas=
es. It=E2=80=99d be funnier if the SEC included a case study where they rea=
d the press release, said =E2=80=9Cah a bottom-line earnings beat,=E2=80=9D=
 bought stock, and then lost money as it went down instead of up.=C2=A0</p>=
