ottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">=
Here is Robin Sloan</a>:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A larg=
e fraction of Web3=E2=80=99s magnetism comes from the value of the underlyi=
ng cryptocurrencies. Therefore, a good diagnostic question to ask might be:=
 would you still be curious about Web3 if those currencies were worthless, =
in dollar terms? For some people, the answer is =E2=80=9Cyes, absolutely=E2=
=80=9D, because they would still find the foundational puzzles compelling. =
For others, if they=E2=80=99re honest, the answer is =E2=80=9Cnnnot reallyy=
y=E2=80=9D.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I sympathize with =
the =E2=80=9Cthis is bad=E2=80=9D camp, but to be fair I don=E2=80=99t own =
any wildly appreciated tokens and might just be jealous. I do want to talk =
about incentives though. Think about traditional =E2=80=9CWeb2=E2=80=9D soc=
ial networks. If you are a user, and someone shows you a new social network=
, you will probably use it if you find it good and not use it if you don=E2=
=80=99t. =E2=80=9CGood=E2=80=9D here means some combination of (1) you like=
 its features and design and (2) network effects (your friends are on it). =
And maybe there is some interaction between those things where you are more=
 likely to use a network if you think=C2=A0<em>other people=C2=A0</em>will =
like its features and design, so that you think it will build a large netwo=
rk.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Meanwhile traditional social networks w=
ere funded by venture capitalists. If you are a VC, and someone shows you a=
 social network, you will probably fund it if you think that other people w=
ill like its features and design and it will build a large network. Investo=
rs, like users, will evaluate the project based on the intrinsic quality an=
d desirability of its product.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But what abo=
ut a Web3 social network? If someone shows you a Web3 social network, your =
decision about whether to use it will depend on (1) its goodness, (2) its u=
sefulness as a network and (3)=C2=A0<em>your odds of getting rich</em>. Poi=
nt (3) is the new one, and it seems to dominate: If you are the sort of per=
son who chooses to use a new social network that promises to pay people for=
 posting, it's probably because you like money more than you like posting.<=
/p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">As you evaluate a new Web3 social network, =
how do you calculate your odds of getting rich? Well, you get rich if the n=
etwork becomes popular, so you are =E2=80=94=C2=A0like a Web2=C2=A0VC =E2=
=80=94=C2=A0evaluating the network=E2=80=99s odds of taking off and becomin=
g huge. You are trying to figure out if=C2=A0<em>other=C2=A0</em>people wil=
l like the network and want to use it.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But =
notice that=C2=A0<em>your=C2=A0</em>decision was in large part=C2=A0about t=
he money. So everyone else=E2=80=99s probably will be too, recursively. You=
r decision to join a Web3 project depends mostly on your expectation of get=
ting rich, which depends on your expectation about other people joining, wh=
ich depends on your expectation about their expectation of getting rich, wh=
ich depends on your expectation about their expectation about other people =
joining, which depends on your expectation about their expectation about th=
eir expectation of getting rich, which etc.=C2=A0Only mostly! The intrinsic=
 desirability of the project matters too. But the money seems pretty import=
ant.=C2=A0=E2=80=9CCrypto projects tend to rely on some form of momentum, w=
here one cohort of participants gets involved because the previous cohort g=
ot rich,=E2=80=9D <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/=
26123257.256657/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cudGhlZGlmZi5jby9wL2NyeXB0by1kYW9zLWFuZC1lY29=
ub21pYy1pcC1wcm90ZWN0aW9uP3Rva2VuPWV5SjFjMlZ5WDJsa0lqb3hNRFkzTUN3aWNHOXpkRj=
lwWkNJNk5EVTNOVFV4T1RJc0lsOGlPaUl4U25velVTSXNJbWxoZENJNk1UWTBNREF3TkRZeU15d=
2laWGh3SWpveE5qUXdNREE0TWpJekxDSnBjM01pT2lKd2RXSXRNVGswTXpBaUxDSnpkV0lpT2lK=
d2IzTjBMWEpsWVdOMGFXOXVJbjAuaXVhUmY3VFhRWEtOZzJjbGJTeDdHYjRicEE3eEt0Z01IcEM=
wYzI4SlA3cw/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB378b8111" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" items=
cope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decorati=
